fields.content:
The Hobart Games Society (HoGS) is a games club that meets weekly in the greater city of Hobart, Tasmania to play tabletop (board and card) games and promote the hobby of tabletop gaming as an inclusive entertainment option that is interactive, stimulating and brings people together, while remaining affrodable, accessible and popular across all ages, sexes and cultures.

HoGS is about every person who comes through the door at one of our regular meet-ups or special events. Our club is run by volunteers, including our Committee and others who regularly donate their time to see that the doors are open when scheduled, and closed accordingly, that free coffee and tea facilities are available, and more.
fields.title: About Us

fields.content:
HoGS meet-ups are held almost every weekend somewhere in the greater Hobart area. Check our calendar or Facebook group for dates and locations.

Your first visit is FREE. Then, we ask for a $5 donation at any regular meet-up to help defray hall hire expenses.

Or, for less than the cost of one meet-up/month, become a Supporting Member and attend ALL regular meet-ups throughout the membership year.
